# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# DUAL-REPO PRIVATE-NOTES GUARD (operator workflow preserved)
# Per canonical ~/0_MOBIUS.TILES/docs/plans/dual_repo_canonical_runbook_
#     and_pitfalls_for_tiles_and_nvr_2026_05_29.md §3
#
# DESIGN: most operator-private docs stay TRACKED in the private repo
# (operator's audit trail + the `commit` alias depends on `git add .`).
# The leak is prevented at PUBLISH TIME by scripts/publish_public_mirror.sh
# (layer 3) which filter-repo's them out of the cleansed public history,
# AND by .githooks/pre-push (layer 2) which differentiates remotes and
# refuses to push these paths to a public remote URL.
#
# Only files that should be untracked EVERYWHERE (operator does not
# version them at all) go in the gitignore block below.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Untracked everywhere — operator never wants these versioned
chat.md
claude_rules.md
DOCS/
.tag

# Operator-private dirs that have caused leaks elsewhere in the portfolio
# (TILES learned the hard way — MSG-300 canonical pitfall). Defensive
# entries: not tracked here today, but guards against an accidental commit
# from running infrastructure (e.g. a stray docker volume mount).
_SYNCAPP/
.hubitat/
postgres_data/

# Operator dump files (defensive — not tracked here today)
app_structure.txt
claude_rules.txt
file_history.txt
tree.txt

# Allowlist: scripts and hooks that MUST stay tracked (filename matches
# patterns the operator might add globally elsewhere). Keeps the
# publish/auto-version surface visible in the private repo.
!scripts/publish_public_mirror.sh
!scripts/_auto_version.sh
!.githooks/pre-push
!.githooks/pre-commit
